    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-21T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-21T20:00:00-05:00" n="679"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d679">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.20/608: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Hong Kong</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Donovan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-21T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 21, 1937—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your August 21, 2 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>In accordance with Department’s telegraphic circular instruction of August
                        10, 6 p.m.,<note n="7" xml:id="d679fn7">Not printed, but see letter of
                            August 11 to the Secretary of War, <ref target="frus1937v01#pg_871">vol.
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 871</ref>.</note> endorse
                        passports as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“This passport is not valid for travel to or in any foreign state in
                                connection with entrance into or service in foreign military or
                                naval forces.”</p>
                        </quote>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Also call the attention of the Americans in question to the provisions of
                        Section 221, Title 22, U. S. Code, and of Section 4090 Revised
                        Statutes.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Confine your action within the limits set forth in paragraphs 1 and 2
                        above and refer the question as to departure from Hong Kong airport of
                        Americans concerned to decision of airport authorities.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
